From b780b5dda62b544685f8fc16a8f8316e32d9137c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Luis Henrique Silva Cazuriaga
 <LuisHenrique.SilvaCazuriaga@windriver.com>
Date: Tue, 10 Mar 2026 15:19:43 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] Add PVC support for nova ephemeral storage.

Add a Nova PersistentVolumeClaim template for ephemeral instances storage.

When storage_conf.pvc.enabled=true, create the claim and mount it in nova-compute and libvirt daemonsets.

The mount target follows `storage_conf.pvc.instances_path` for nova and libvirt.

NFS and PVC mounts are mutually exclusive in all ephemeral storage mount points.

PVC name, size, access modes, and storage class are read from storage_conf.pvc.*.

Change-Id: I3311e53ee2a97e87c40af7b79b1d230efe34a5af
[ Adapt OSH patches to Gazpacho release ]
Signed-off-by: Daniel Caires <DanielMarques.Caires@windriver.com>
[ Add a comment for storage_class_priority ]
Signed-off-by: Raghu Sarangapani <raghu.sarangapani@windriver.com>
---
 libvirt/templates/daemonset-libvirt.yaml | 10 ++++++++++
 libvirt/values.yaml                      |  4 ++++
 nova/templates/daemonset-compute.yaml    | 19 +++++++++++++++++++
 nova/templates/pvc-nova-ephemeral.yaml   | 23 +++++++++++++++++++++++
 nova/values.yaml                         | 22 +++++++++++++++++++++-
 5 files changed, 77 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)
 create mode 100644 nova/templates/pvc-nova-ephemeral.yaml

diff --git a/libvirt/templates/daemonset-libvirt.yaml b/libvirt/templates/daemonset-libvirt.yaml
index 12edfde..a482571 100644
